                        while using <strong>"Endnode/Wall Eraser"</strong> button will allow you to remove End nodes.</p>
                        <img class="modal-body-image3" src="images/Modal-MultipleEndnodes.png"/>
                        <p></p>
                        <h5 class="modal-subtitle"> Select PathFinding Algorithm Then Run!</h5>
                        <p> Select any of the avaialable algorithms in <strong>"PathFinding Algorithms"</strong> selection then finally press the <strong>"Run"</strong> button beside it.</p>
                        <img class="modal-body-image2" src="images/Modal-ChooseAndPlaySearch.png"/>
                    break;

                    case 3:
                        <h1 class="modal-h1"style="color:#A3A300">Manual</h1>
                        <h1 class="modal-h2" style="color:green">Interacting with The Algorithm</h1>
                        <h5 class="modal-subtitle"> Buttons</h5>
                        <p> Buttons has 3 states: <strong>disabled</strong>, <strong>clickable</strong>, and <strong>active</strong>. 
                        Buttons states are reflected on the appearance which can be seen with he marked image below:</p>
                        <img class="modal-body-image3" src="images/Modal-ButtonStatesMarked.png"/>
                        <p></p>
                        <h5 class="modal-subtitle"> Pause and Reset</h5>
