                        <p><strong> Recursive Depth-First Search (DFS)</strong> - Searches as deep as possible in one direction before back-tracking. This one has a feature that <strong>marks dead ends </strong> in the grid. Does not gurantee shortest path</p>
                        <p><strong> A* Search</strong> - Performs a smart heuristic search where it evaluates each of the nodes to be explored based on distance both to end node and start node. <strong>Guarantees the shortest path</strong> possible but requires the end node location to be known. </p>
                        <p><strong> Greedy Best-First Search</strong> - A heuristic search but only prioritizes nodes that are closer to an end node. Does not gurantee shortest path but requires the end node location to be known</p>
                        <p><strong> Bidirectional Search</strong> - Does 2 simultaneous search from start node and endnode. Selecting this <strong>limits end nodes to 1</strong>. But it <strong>guarantees the shortest path</strong> possible.</p>
