                        <p><strong> Iterative Backtracker</strong> - Carves out path in a winding, snake like manner. It moves in random directions until it hits an dead end, then backtracks until the entire grid is explored</p>
                        <p><strong>  Kruskal's</strong> - Closes the grid with walls, leaving 1 x 1 openings. It then connects the openings until all are traversable.</p>
                    break;
